This paper discusses the problem of disinformation on Wikipedia and proposes solutions to combat it. It involves interdisciplinary research from fields such as journalism, sociology, philosophy, information and political sciences, which suggests that it could fall under the category of cs.CY (Computers and Society) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques to detect potentially dangerous content, which could place it under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper discusses the role of Wikipedia in combating disinformation, which could place it under cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks).
